\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1.1}{\ignorespaces Four different multicopters. Fig. \ref {fig:racingDrone} is kind of a VTOL itself, due to its high vertical speed.}}{2}{figure.caption.5}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1.2}{\ignorespaces Two Fixed Wing UAVs. The General Atomics MQ9 Reaper (left). Zipline Platform 1 remote delivery aircraft during takeoff (right)}}{2}{figure.caption.6}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1.3}{\ignorespaces Four different commercial and defense eVTOL aircraft in various stages of development and use. Each design is specialized to the use case and developer's design philosophy. Figs. \ref {fig:archer} and \ref {fig:BetaTech} are commercial eVTOL air taxis in development from Archer Aviation and Beta Technologies, respectively. The V-22 Osprey in Fig. \ref {fig:osprey} is a famous VTOL that has seen extensive use by the U.S. Military. Fig. \ref {fig:zipline} is the Zipline VTOL, which is under development for food and package delivery.}}{4}{figure.caption.7}%
